\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {8}{\ignorespaces Throughput (RPS) across the full agent$\times $concurrency sweep ($n = 5$ repetitions per cell, error bars 95\% CI). Each panel fixes an agent count and varies concurrency on a log axis. The relative ordering is stable across all five panels, and none of the three systems collapses inside the tested window.}}{36}{figure.8}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:chapter4-throughput-sweep}{{8}{36}{Throughput (RPS) across the full agent$\times $concurrency sweep ($n = 5$ repetitions per cell, error bars 95\% CI). Each panel fixes an agent count and varies concurrency on a log axis. The relative ordering is stable across all five panels, and none of the three systems collapses inside the tested window}{figure.8}{}}
